    <keyword>pmem</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">&gt;&gt;&gt; Evaluate Address</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">At the <text styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt;</text> prompt the SRM console can read and write memory directly -- useful for inspecting device CSRs and firmware state during debugging.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Examine (e)</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">e &lt;space&gt;:&lt;address&gt;</text> reads a location and prints its value. The <text styleclass="Code Example">pmem:</text> space addresses physical memory (including device / chipset MMIO):</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt; e pmem:80130000040</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">pmem: 80130000040 0000000000000000</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Deposit (d)</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">d &lt;space&gt;:&lt;address&gt; &lt;value&gt;</text> writes a value to a location:</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt; d pmem:80130000040 1</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">These are the commands behind the halt-gate diagnostics (for example the arming read of <text styleclass="Code Example">pmem:80130000FF8</text>). Be precise with the address and space prefix; an address that is not in an executable region is rejected (&quot;not executable&quot;), and a malformed line produces a syntax error.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="SeeAlso">See Also.</text></para>
